Title:
Day 33 – Expanded conversational Spanish + multi-source reinforcement

Summary:

Practiced and refined 10 core conversational phrases focused on everyday interactions and “getting to know someone” topics
Reinforced correct sentence structures including:
“llevar + time” (e.g., llevo aquí dos horas)
proper use of me gusta / no me gusta
correct question structure and word order
Identified and corrected recurring grammar issues:
verb conjugations (e.g., vengo vs vieno)
gender agreement (pequeño/pequeña, ruidoso/ruidosa)
proper use of accents (por qué, está, qué)
Completed Duolingo and Memrise vocabulary:
ordinal numbers (segundo, tercero, cuarto, etc.)
emotional and descriptive words (extraño, contento)
Continued Pimsleur review (Unit 1, Lessons 7–10):
pricing, time, and basic conversational phrases
questions like ¿Cuánto cuesta? and ¿Cuánto dinero tienes?
Added real-world restaurant interaction phrases:
¿Hablas español?
¿Puedo practicar mi español contigo?
Mi español no es muy bueno todavía
Completed Mango lessons:
descriptive vocabulary (ruidoso, lleno de gente, zona peligrosa)
situational phrases for public places and environments
Completed multiple quiz rounds covering:
conversation
grammar corrections
real-world usage
Improved ability to respond naturally without relying on memorized scripts


